Extracción de datos¶

In [2]:
start = datetime.datetime(2010, 1, 1)
end = datetime.datetime(2017, 1, 1)
In [3]:
BBVA = data.DataReader('BBVA.MC', 'yahoo', start, end).drop(['High','Low','Open','Volume','Adj Close'],axis=1).rename(columns={'Close':'BBVA'})
BKT = data.DataReader('BKT.MC', 'yahoo', start, end).drop(['High','Low','Open','Volume','Adj Close'],axis=1).rename(columns={'Close':'BKT'})
CABK = data.DataReader('CABK.MC', 'yahoo', start, end).drop(['High','Low','Open','Volume','Adj Close'],axis=1).rename(columns={'Close':'CABK'})
SAB = data.DataReader('SAB.MC', 'yahoo', start, end).drop(['High','Low','Open','Volume','Adj Close'],axis=1).rename(columns={'Close':'SAB'})
SAN = data.DataReader('SAN.MC', 'yahoo', start, end).drop(['High','Low','Open','Volume','Adj Close'],axis=1).rename(columns={'Close':'SAN'})

val_banc = pd.concat([BBVA, BKT, CABK, SAB, SAN],axis=1)
val_banc.index.names = ['Fecha']
In [4]:
val_banc = val_banc.iloc[1:]
val_banc=val_banc.asfreq('b')
val_banc=val_banc.fillna(method='ffill')

Obteniendo Rendimientos¶

In [5]:
val_banc['rend_cabk'] = val_banc.CABK.pct_change(1).mul(100)
val_banc['rend_san'] = val_banc.SAN.pct_change(1).mul(100)
val_banc['rend_sab'] = val_banc.SAB.pct_change(1).mul(100)
val_banc['rend_bbva'] = val_banc.BBVA.pct_change(1).mul(100)
val_banc['rend_bkt'] = val_banc.BKT.pct_change(1).mul(100)
In [6]:
val_banc['norm_rend_cabk'] = val_banc.rend_cabk.div(val_banc.rend_cabk[1])*100
val_banc['norm_rend_san'] = val_banc.rend_san.div(val_banc.rend_san[1])*100
val_banc['norm_rend_sab'] = val_banc.rend_sab.div(val_banc.rend_sab[1])*100
val_banc['norm_rend_bbva'] = val_banc.rend_bbva.div(val_banc.rend_bbva[1])*100
val_banc['norm_rend_bkt'] = val_banc.rend_bkt.div(val_banc.rend_bkt[1])*100

size = 1563

Ajustando un primer modelo¶

Se comienza probando el modelo más simple y se sigue probando con modelos más complicados.

Probando el caso más simple, el auto regresivo.

In [8]:
model_ar = ARIMA(df.SAN, order = (1,0,0))
results_ar = model_ar.fit()

Empleando el rendimiento¶

In [13]:

Auto ARIMA¶

En este caso de aplicación, los parámetros son ajustados tras numerosas pruebas. Solo es necesario indicar el valor hasta el cual se quiere llegar a probar.

In [23]:
model_auto = auto_arima(df.rend_san[1:], exogenous = df[['rend_cabk', 'rend_sab', 'rend_bbva']][1:],
                       m = 5, max_p = 5, max_q = 5, max_P = 5, max_Q = 5)
In [24]:
df_auto_pred = pd.DataFrame(model_auto.predict(n_periods = len(df_test[start_date:end_date]),
                            exogenous = df_test[['rend_cabk', 'rend_sab', 'rend_bbva']][start_date:end_date]),
                            index = df_test[start_date:end_date].index)
In [25]:
df_auto_pred.plot(figsize = (20,5), color = "red")
df_test.rend_san[start_date:end_date].plot(color = "blue")
plt.title("Predicción modelo automático vs Datos Reales", size = 24)
plt.show()

Comparando los modelos para el rendimiento¶

Se comparan todos los modelos a la vez para así saber cual emplear.

In [26]:
ar = df_pred_ar[start_date:end_date]
ma = df_pred_ma[start_date:end_date]
arma = df_pred_arma[start_date:end_date]
armax = df_pred_armax[start_date:end_date]
sarma = df_pred_sarma[start_date:end_date]
sarimax = df_pred_sarimax[start_date:end_date]
real = df_test.rend_san[start_date:end_date]
ts_red_preds = pd.concat([ar, ma, armax, sarma, sarimax,real],axis=1,
                         keys=['ar', 'ma', 'armax', 'sarma', 'sarimax','real'])
ts_red_preds.to_csv('prediccion1.csv')


ar.plot(figsize = (20,10), color = "yellow")

arma.plot(color = "cyan")
armax.plot(color = "green")
sarma.plot(color = "magenta")

real.plot(color = "blue")
plt.legend(['AR','MA','ARMA','ARMAX','SARMA','SARIMAX'])
plt.title("Todos los modelos", size = 24)

Prediciendo la volatilidad¶

Para el modelo GARCH se puede demostrar matematicamente que no es posible mejorar el caso para $p=1$ y $q=1$

In [28]:
mod_garch = arch_model(val_banc.rend_san[1:], vol = "GARCH", p = 1, q = 1, mean = "constant", dist = "Normal")
res_garch = mod_garch.fit(last_obs = start_date, update_freq = 5)

Iteration:      5,   Func. Count:     39,   Neg. LLF: 3321.006719020473
Optimization terminated successfully    (Exit mode 0)

            Function evaluations: 58
            Gradient evaluations: 9
In [29]:
pred_garch = res_garch.forecast(horizon = 1, align = 'target')
In [30]:
pred_garch.residual_variance[start_date:].plot(figsize = (20,5), color = "red", zorder = 2)
df_test.rend_san.abs().plot(color = "blue", zorder = 1)
plt.title("Predicción de volatilidad", size = 24)
plt.show()

garch = pred_garch.residual_variance[start_date:]
vol_true = df_test.rend_san.abs()

vol = pd.concat([garch,vol_true],axis=1)
vol.to_csv('prediccion2.csv')
